This project reuses files from the `zkp_ecc` project published on Zenodo.

Reused verbatim (unmodified):

    src/circuit.rs                     (from lib/src/circuit.rs)
    src/weierstrass_elliptic_curve.rs  (from lib/src/weierstrass_elliptic_curve.rs)

Reused with modifications (derived work under CC BY 4.0):

    src/sim.rs                         (from lib/src/sim.rs)
        Modified the `R` (free / measure-and-reset) op handler to ASSERT
        that its target qubit is |0⟩ across all live shots before zeroing,
        and to return `Result<(), String>` from `apply` / `apply_iter` /
        `apply_archived` so the caller can surface assertion failures.
        The upstream version unconditionally zeros the target, which
        permits "dirty free" of an ancilla as a silent reversibility bug.
        This research project enforces strict reversibility, so R is
        promoted to a hard correctness check at the simulator level.
        The change is purely defensive — when the input circuit is
        already clean, the modified sim produces identical results to
        the upstream version.

